just_use db.go

# label: CANONICAL
# role: encodes domain knowledge

Single-connection SQLite (SetMaxOpenConns(1)) — serializes all access so
there's no lock contention, no WAL/SHM sidecar files, and every package
shares the one `DB` var without coordination. Fine for our traffic level.

seedData() hardcodes four users (Steve, Apoorva, Claude, Joe) with fixed
api_keys. These are test fixtures that ship in demo mode only; prod sets
GOPHER_RESET_DB=1 explicitly or never at all. Schema comes from
schema.Core — no migrations, rebuild on change.
